Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C.

Cut the @sweet potato{2} lengthways into 1cm slices, then cut into 1cm wide fries
(no need to peel). Pop onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}(for
fries), season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out in a
single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, put the @Mexican style spice mix{1} @panko breadcrumbs{10}, 
@water{2} and @salt{1/4%tsp} into a large #bowl{}, then mix to combine.

Add the @British beef mince{360%g}, season with pepper and mix together with
your hands. Roll the mince into even-sized balls, then shape into 2cm thick
burgers (1 per person).

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop the burgers onto a lightly oiled baking tray and bake on the middle shelf
of your oven until cooked through, ~{18-20%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While they bake, heat a drizzle of @oil{}(for frying) in a large #frying pan{}
on medium-high heat. When hot, add the @chorizo{60%g} and fry until it starts
to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}, then transfer to a small bowl and set aside.

Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}. Trim the @baby gem{1}, then separate the
leaves. Grate the @mature Cheddar cheese{90%g}. Halve the @burger buns{2}.

In a small bowl, combine the @mayonnaise{32%g} and half the @chipotle paste{5%g},
then set the chipotle mayo aside.

Put the @olive oil{1} in another large bowl, season to taste with salt and
pepper. Add the tomatoes, mix together, then set aside.

About ~{4-5%minutes} before the burgers and fries are ready, carefully place
half the cheese on top of the burgers.

Sprinkle the chorizo and remaining cheese over the fries and return both trays
to the oven to allow the cheese to melt, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Pop the burger buns onto a baking tray and into the oven to warm through,
~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything is ready, add the baby gem to the tomatoes, then toss together.

Spoon the chipotle mayo onto each bun base, then top with a cheesy burger and
close with the bun lid.

Serve the burgers with the loaded fries and salad alongside. Enjoy!